Guinea is a country that has given a lot to the world and that is still not riding the wave. Some would link this to the precariousness of the leadership and would argue that institutionalised corruption has prevented modernisation of certain essential sectors of the economy, most notably mining, agriculture, shipping and the chaotic atlantic ports. Most people think that people Rose-2010 to high positions and positions in the government have done a very bad job during their 6-year rule before finally losing their positions of power in 2014.

It is extremely important that we have a proper democratic working system, the country can not afford that. We will have a realistic chance to bring in a new generation of leaders that can and will get along and work for the people. Working with local and international influencers to enable promotion of education, ensure real reconciliation and independence from homelessness and poverty and make sure that no one comes in comes in the country to do harm as opposed to good.
